these are all routines from the CERN mathlib for the polygamma
function wpsipg(z,n)

changes wrt to CERN version:

- converted to quad-precision
- added Bernouli coefficients up to order 12, reaching deviations lower than 1E-27 to analytical Fermi function
  (beta=2000)

documentation can be found at
hep.fi.infn.it/cernlib.pdf (last checked: october 2nd 2018)

wpsipg(z,0) = psi(z) = d(ln(Gamma(z)))/dz <- digamma function
wpsipg(z,k) = psi^k (z) = d^k/dz^k psi(z) <- polygamma function
  k element 1...4
